<bug>
    <id>369074</id>
    <title>Check4change plugin is not working as expected</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">I have installed the check4change plugin.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">But it is not working as expected.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">I have selected the text to be monitored and enabled the check4changed.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">But 
without any change in the text also, when the page refreshes (after the stipulated time that was set for monitoring) was over, mozilla pops up one
window notifying that a change has been identified.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.5">But when I checked that page, I could not find any change.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">1 Select text in a web page.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">Choose check4change option for that web page.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.4">2 Set the monitoring time to 60 sec through custom option.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.5">3 Check all the options in monitoring category and check the box "bring to</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.6">front" in notifications category.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.7">Actual Results:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.8">Whenever the stipulated time expires, irrespective of the change in the web</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.9">browser, one pop up window appears notifiying that a change has been identified.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Expected Results:  
Pop up window must and should appear only when a change is identified not after
every time interval.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
